values: wow.....I forgot this place even existed....it was a lifetime ago.....

well, I mean, I moved home, I'm living in Milwaukee, so far I've hated every second of it, but I think it'll get better :)

Maybe just another winter or two to finally convince to move out of here for more than a month...apparently Savannah just wasn't for me, even if I did meet the man I'm gonna marry whilst I was down there....ok that's all....

note to self: the south is REALLY hot and REALLY humid...BUT Savannah is beautiful so I'll deal...still tryin' to find a job but I have high hopes that I won't ever have to return to WI again!  I know I always said it'd be California, but I think Georgia suits me just fine..and I haven't run into any crazy "I love the confederate flag and won't eat anything but grits" southerners yet..maybe I just haven't gotten out enough, but so far, things are going well...AND I get to go to the ocean next week! Yay for me :o)
I'm moving to Georgia on Wednesday!! crazy....

WELL...I decided to come back...mainly so that I can look back in 10 years and view my entries and laugh at what an idiot I was...

My life in a nutshell...I finally graduated in May with a BA in Psychology and a minor in Family and Health Studies...I'm living at home in Stevens Point until the end of July, at which point, I will be moving to Savannah, Georgia....ok that's all for now

Grad school possibilities so far: 
Iowa State
Loyola in Chicago
Northern Iowa
Northern Illinois
Indiana University
UW-Madison
NC State
Penn State
....thoughts, suggestions? 

And yesterday, it was confirmed...I have two classes left to take next semester and then I GRADUATE!!!

...I guess I really have to grow up now
Whoever said growing up and doing things like applying for grad schools was fun LIED to me!

nothing makes me happier than driving around in a terrential downpour with the streets flooded and splashing students with my car...well, because I can....

ok that's all

I deleted...and then felt sad....but for real, I'm deleting this damn thing really soon...I pretty much have no use for it anymore other than to stalk people and that pretty much needs to stop now....

also..turning 22..isn't all that great...but it did provide me with some great new pictures for icons!! :o)

TWO DAYS UNTIL MY BIRTHDAY....god I'm amazing ;o)


Also...just had my first official visit with Teege since moving back...and he's great and I've missed him....and he made a BOOK out of his livejournal so ALL of his posts are in it and it's basically amazing...I think I'm gonna do that so I can finally delete LJ without deleting my memories....

basically, it sucks to hang onto something for WAY TOO LONG and then have to finally realize that it's just time to let go.....so my advice to all of you, let go sooner rather than later ;o)


also...I'm going to Texas Roadhouse to celebrate my birthday and they make me ride a saddle and I'm not gonna lie, I'm pretty excited ;o)

peace out....

black nail polish is really a pain in the ass to get off....but do you know what really sucks?  Dumping half a bottle of nail polish remover on yourself


I turn 22 on Sunday and I basically feel old because I didn't actually think I'd make it past 19....either way, I'm going out to the amazing establishments in downtown Whitewater on Saturday night and you're all more than welcome to come..even if you have to find a fake ID to do so ;o)

ok peace out

my brother's wedding was pretty amazing...


and I caught the bouqet....


and now I'm clearly gonna get married soon and life is great ;o)

So...who's excited to get really sunburnt over the next two weeks from the tanning bed so that she can have even skin to stand up in her Jesus brother's wedding in Georgia??  That'd be me :o)

And who's even more excited because I have an idea of places for grad school...which include places in Arizona, North Carolina, possibly Virginia...and maybe a few others....all of which do NOT include Wisconsin....and this of course also means I'm graduating in a year...never really thought that day would come....time to prep for the GRE's! :o(

I'm also quite excited to be an Orientation Leader this summer..it's a change of pace from being an RA and opened up a lot of different opportunities for my future in Student Affairs..so yay for me....

And can I just say I forgot what I was missing by having an oven 10 feet away from me instead of having to go down to 1st floor and then having to sit next to the oven and then bringing my food back up to my room....apartment life is great!


Mmm...ok...that's all for now...peace out homeslices :o)

tonight is officially my last night as an RA....

...and I couldn't be sadder.....

Yellowcard concert tonight = AMAZING

Remind me to never go into the semi-moshing but not really moshing at all area AGAIN...I HURT right now ;)  I'm an old lady....

So...I went to Madison this weekend with every intent of going to Mifflin for awhile and then going to the bars at night....neither happened as my friend Jenn and I were completely annoyed that we were SOAKING wet, so we just sat in Noodles for two hours and had a great conversation as pathetic as that sounds....we walked PAST Mifflin, decided we weren't drunk enough to venture down that road, and kept going down to State Street....whilst we were doing this, we saw someone get hit by a car.....

I also went to Ian's Pizza for the very first time on Saturday night and it was AMAZING....


And who's excited to go see O.A.R. tonight??...that'd be me!!!


Happy May 2nd to all of you ;)

Anyone wanna go to a Brewer game with me tomorrow? Anyone? Anyone?  Free tickets from my good friend Sam...and they're good tickets...and I have nobody to go with so I will not be going and I'm a little sad...


OK GOODBYE

Have I mentioned that even though my bible-thumping brother tells me I'm a sinner on a regular basis, he's getting married in June and I couldn't be more excited??


Have I also mentioned I only have 6 weeks left of being an RA and the bittersweet feelings are setting in....

Have I also mentioned how excited I am to be an Orientation Leader this summer so I can mold the incoming freshman depending on whether or not I like their RA....ok I wouldn't really do that, calm down....but I am excited for the job....

Have I also mentioned how great it is to have basically a brand new computer as it now has a brand new processor and was totally reformatted and now it doesn't just shut off at random points during the day NOR freeze up!  Have I also mentioned how much it sucks when your dad THINKS he backed up ALL of your files, when in fact he only backed up half of them so now the other half of my documents are gone forever?....


Ok that's all for now...

Hope you're all having wonderful lives...I know I am!

It's always a little depressing to come home at 5 a.m. and get an IM, from your old co whom you haven't spoken to in months...and the IM is one line and one line only and it went a little something like this

czukster: I still don't like you



Thanks Jimmy....thanks.....


oh and by the way..it's Spring Break and I couldn't be happier to get away!!

Oh if things couldn't get better!  My grandma has to have a triple bypass....

She told the doctor's that she would have to 'get back to them' as to when she could schedule surgery because she has a husband with health problems....they forced her to make an appt. anyway, thank god.  They asked her what good she'd be to her husband with severe health problems if she died of a heart attack in a month.

I just found out my puppy (she's not really a puppy) has cancer :'(.....


We've had her for 10 years....


I'm really devastated...even if people don't understand why people get so upset about pets...we got her when I was only 11 so I pretty much grew up with her and I really feel like I'm going to lose a family member as dramatic and cheesy as that sounds....the doctor said she'd make it to next spring but won't make it to the fall....

:(

Well, Georgia and South Carolina were actually really amazing....I'm not much of one for anything Southern, but sometimes you just have to deal with it when your brother is in the south.

We flew into Atlanta on Christmas day, drove to Athens to see my brother and meet his girlfriend and then pretty much went right to bed....then the excitement began the next day as we got to meet Nathaniel's girlfriend's (he'll be marrying her eventually) family and they cooked us a traditional southern Christmas dinner...her mother is probably the most intimidating woman I've ever met and she's SUPER controlling of her only daughter, so I guess good luck goes out to my brother....her whole family was really nice though so we all just looked past the fact that we knew her mother probably wanted nothing to do with us...

Then the real fun of my trip began...we went to Savannah, Georgia.  I've decided I should've been a history major.  Savannah was just full of history and I loved every second of it.  We spent two days walking around/driving around/riding in a trolley car/sitting by the water and watching GIANT ships come in from the ocean in Savannah.  My parents are thinking about moving there and if I had to pick any place in the south for them to live, it'd be there.  It's full of history and right on the water which is important..and even though they'd probably never make friends down there because they're 'from the north', it's fine, they don't have friends up here anyway ;).  I did a lot of thinking about life when I was there and came to many new conclusions about myself and people because it was really just a peaceful place for me.  I ALSO got to see places where parts of Midnight in the Garden of Good and Evil and Forrest Gump and The Legend of Bagger Vance and a few other movies were filmed...and we all know how big of a movie freak I am, so that was fun.  And P.S., Forrest Gump's bus stop bench, wasn't really real, they knocked down a little wall and took out shrubbery in one of the 21 'squares' or parkish things in Savannah and made it look like a bus stop.  I learned a lot of other things about those movies there, but I won't bore you with even more details.  

We then headed to Hilton Head, South Carolina.  It was about a 45 minute drive.  We spent time with my Dad's family in the seasonal home they own there.  The only part I really loved about HH is that they're family we've never really spent time with because my dad's mom was CRAZY so we stayed away from his side of the family....she died awhile ago, but we just never made attempts after that to spend time with his family.  Hilton Head is basically just one GIANT resort town.  It's just golf course after golf course (one of which my aunt and uncle live on) and tourists everywhere, no matter what time of year.  It was fun to be on the ocean and spend time with the family, but I would've rather stayed in Savnnah a few days longer.

All in all, it was a great trip and I even bonded a little with my brother (which we all know doesn't happen much anymore).  I learned a lot about myself during this trip and kind of have a new outlook on so many things.  Who knew travelling to the south could do that to a person....and don't worry, my new life lessons have nothing to do with following Southern traditions or politics or anything like that because that would be frightening...I just happened to learn something about life whilst in the south...

Also, I chopped my hair off (I swear to god I'm not trying to copy you Katie) yesterday and put highlights in again...and now, for me at least, I'm blond.  Of course the rest of you probably won't think so, but putting blonde and light brown highlights in REALLY lightens as dark of hair as I have....

OK PEACE OUT

MERRY CHRISTMAS!!! :)

Don't worry, I am writing this in Georgia right now, which means I didn't die in a plane crash!

Hope you all have a wonderful week :)

Well I just wanted to wish you all a Happy Chrismahanukwanzakah!!!


I finally get to leave this place...only to travel to Georgia/South Carolina to visit my Southern Baptist *shudders* brother and spend some QT with the family...I'm a little sad that I won't get to have a snow-filled Christmas AND I'm spending Christmas day in airports, but shit happens....and THEN I get to come back to Whitewater for New Year's and I'm actually pretty excited about going to the bars until 6 a.m.!

Then I only get a week of rest at home (when I will finally be back online and I KNOW you'll all be waiting by your computers for me) and then I'm back here for RA training....not a very long break, but I'm sure I'll start missing my home here in WW around then and it'll be good to get back....



PEACE OUT :-D

P.S. - I miss all of you crazy residents already and I hope you have a wonderful break...be sure to call me lots because this bitch has nationwide calling and you won't even have to miss hearing my voice whilst I'm in Georgia! :-D  I know...you just peed in your pants Caitlin VDV because you're so excited ;)
well...the lease is signed...goodbye RA and hello DLK...I'm living in the New Regent apartments, by the way...close to classes AND the bars..what could be better? ;)

It feels a little weird to update considering I haven't done so in a month....


Can I just say that all-nighters are NEVER a good idea!!  But at least I got two papers done and all of my RA paperwork :-D  Nevermind that the papers are due today and I've had ample time to work on them and that the paperwork was due last week ;)

P.S.....I'm signing my lease TODAY to live off-campus next year....I'm excited as I know I need a year off to explore other things before I venture into a residence life career, but really scared and anxious at the same time....guess we'll just have to see how it goes...boo to selling my soul to DLK though!



HAPPY DECEMBER 1ST - WORLD AIDS DAY AND THE FIRST DAY I GET TO EAT A CHOCOLATE OUT OF MY ADVENT CALENDAR :-d










I miss you....and part of me always will....

I'm not gonna lie that driving to Madison every Friday kind of annoys me....I guess I'll suck it up for 4 more weeks....

I'm also not gonna lie that having an influx of whooping cough and mono on campus is not exactly fun...especially when all of the cases of whooping cough are in Wells and you don't know if people have passed out from alcohol or their sickness :)


OK BYE!!!!!!!!!!!

I understand why you all hate me...

I would hate me too...

I just need to reiterate...PAUL MCCARTNEY WAS AMAZING!!  I was *this close* to crying when Hey Jude, Yesterday, and Let it Be were played....our seats were kind of...behind the stage....but not really......they were just off to the side and we could only see the back of his head except for when he would change guitars (which was frequently) and when he came in and out for his 3, yes 3, encores... and we weren't even far away, just couldn't see the front of the stage other than on the giant screen...the pyrotechnics during Live and Let Die were super except for the fact that all of the smoke dispersed backwards and we were choked momentarily....and it was okay that we were high up because the stage floor had fun lights and technical effects that you couldn't see if you were lower and we always knew when he was about to play the piano because we could see it coming out of the floor....have i mentioned though, that it was spectacular??


Homecoming sucked my will to live.....


In other news, I do not get to have a wonderful white Christmas, as I'm spending my time in Georgia, with my brother telling me that I'm going to go to hell...BUT I get to go to the ocean AND be back in time for a New Year's celebration in Milwaukee!


ok PEACE OUT :-D
The Paul McCartney concert was SPECTACULAR!
